
Program behaviour plan:

1. Initialize calculation (input parameters from user)		(function 1)
	- Particle attributes (position, type, velocity, mass,...)
	- Calculation area limits (X x Y area, wall area)
	- Timestep length
	- Endtime
	- Inflow
	etc
	initial [particle.hh] and [calculation_area.hh]
2. Save datafile initial positioning as time 0			(function 2)
	initial [datafile]
3. Begin Timeloop						(function 3)

---- LOOP (while time < endtime) ----
4. Do particle grouping
5. Calculate forces, acceleration, velocity 			(function 4)
	update [particle.hh]
6. Move particles						(function 5)
	update [particle.hh]
7. Inflow							(function 7)
	update [calculation_area.hh]
	update [particle.hh]
8. Damping loop							(function 8)
9. Check boundaries						(function 6)
10. Save datafile as time x 					(function 2)
	update [datafile]
--- LOOP END -----

11. finish program



Classes:

particle.hh:
[type;
x;
y]



Functions to do:


1.	Particle initial positioning (=initializing calculation)
2.	Write Datafile
3.	Boundary conditions (=delete particles exiting calculation area)
4. 	Density calculation for particles:
		- Grouping
		- Weighted_center
		- Density average
		- Move particles
5.	Calculate acceleration
6.	Calculate velocity
7.	Move Particles according to velocity and acceleration



